{
  "texts": [
    "The test set was evaluated using the fine-tuned model that attained the highest accuracy on the validation set.",
    "We employed an Adam optimizer with a learning rate of 0.0003 for all experiments.",
    "The performance of the classification task was assessed using the macro F1 score metric.Finally, in addition to the adaptations performed in this work, we conducted an extensive grid search involving three hyper-parameters for each of the presented SSL methods using two architectures on the HHAR dataset.",
    "We detail here that all encoders utilize default parameters from the two architectures across all SSL techniques to ensure fairness in the comparison.",
    "For the remaining hyper-parameters, we select those that yielded the lowest loss in each category, and our findings are presented in table 1."
  ]
}